📄 Pages

/getting-started/overview.mdx
# Overview

MeeseeksDiscord v2 lets you forward Discord activity to Telegram.

You can:
- Forward messages based on keywords
- Track member joins
- Monitor tickets

All configuration is done via Telegram.

## Quick Setup

1. Add Discord token(s)
2. Add Telegram bot token(s)
3. Set chat IDs
4. Add keywords
5. Enable features
6. Restart the bot
/getting-started/menu.mdx
# Bot Menu

To configure your bot, open the menu in Telegram:

```bash
/menu

Use the interactive buttons to navigate and configure settings.


---

## `/configuration/discord-tokens.mdx`

```mdx
# Discord Tokens

Add at least one Discord token to start receiving events.

## Limits

- Up to 5 tokens supported

## Fields

- Token 1
- Token 2
- Token 3
- Token 4
- Token 5

## Notes

- At least one token is required
- Duplicate tokens are ignored
- Duplicate events are automatically deduplicated
/configuration/telegram-tokens.mdx
# Telegram Tokens

Configure your Telegram bot tokens.

## Limits

- Up to 3 tokens supported

## Fields

- Token 1 (Primary)
- Token 2 (Fallback)
- Token 3 (Fallback)

## Fallback Logic

If Token 1 fails:
1. Token 2 is used
2. Then Token 3
/configuration/chat-ids.mdx
# Chat IDs

Set where alerts are sent.

## Fields

- Message Chat ID
- Join Chat ID
- Ticket Chat ID

## Supported Formats

```bash
chat_id
chat_id/topic_id
Examples
-1001234567890
-1001234567890/12

---

## `/configuration/keywords.mdx`

```mdx
# Keywords

Keywords control which messages get forwarded.

## Example

```bash
ledger, withdraw, swap, deposit
Behavior
Messages are forwarded only if they match your keywords
Applies to message forwarding only

---

## `/configuration/features.mdx`

```mdx
# Features

Enable or disable bot features.

## Available Features

- Messages
- Member Joins
- Tickets

## Rules

- At least one feature must remain ON
- If a feature is enabled, its Chat ID must be configured
/usage/commands.mdx
# Commands

## Available Commands

| Command        | Description           |
|----------------|-----------------------|
| `/start`       | Open welcome screen   |
| `/menu`        | Open settings menu    |
| `/status`      | Check bot status      |
| `/startbot`    | Start the bot         |
| `/stopbot`     | Stop the bot          |
| `/restartbot`  | Restart the bot       |
/usage/restart.mdx
# Restarting the Bot

You must restart the bot after making changes.

## When to Restart

- Tokens updated
- Chat IDs changed
- Keywords updated
- Features toggled

## How to Restart

### Command

```bash
/restartbot
Or

Use the Restart Bot button in the menu.


---

## `/help/troubleshooting.mdx`

```mdx
# Troubleshooting

## No Discord user token configured

Add at least one token in **Discord Tokens**.

---

## Configure at least one Telegram bot token

Set **Token 1** in Telegram Tokens.

---

## At least one feature must be on

Enable one of:
- Messages
- Member Joins
- Tickets

---

## No forwarded messages

Check:

- Message feature is ON
- Keywords are configured
- Message Chat ID is correct
- Bot was restarted after changes
